# Inventory Management System (Core Three)

## Overview
This project is a **comprehensive Inventory Management System** built using **ASP.NET Core 8 Razor Pages**, **Entity Framework Core**, and **SQL Server**.  
It enables shop owners to manage products, monitor prices, and track historical changes, while offering powerful **exporting, filtering, alerting, and authentication** capabilities.  
It also includes **admin role management**, **user profiles**, **API endpoints with CSRF + rate limiting**, and **a modern, responsive interface**.

---

## 🎯 Key Objectives
The system was designed for small-to-medium shops to streamline inventory tracking by providing:
- A user-friendly web interface for managing stock and price history.
- Secure access control through user roles (Admin, Owner).
- Automated alerts for significant price changes.
- Data export and integration-ready API endpoints.

---

## 🧩 Core Features
### Inventory & Product Management
- Add, edit, view, and delete products with validation.
- Product fields: **Name**, **Owner**, **Price**, optional **Model** and **Category**.
- **Real-time price tracking** with a dedicated `PriceHistory` table.
- Sorting and pagination for long product lists.
- Advanced search by name, category, model, price range, or created date.

### Price History & Alerts
- Automatic **PriceHistory** entries whenever prices are updated.
- **Alert system** triggers when price changes exceed a configurable threshold (default: 10%).
- Dedicated **Alerts page** and **Dashboard summaries** for tracking recent alerts and top categories.

### Data Export
- Export **Products** and **Price History** to:
  - **CSV** (standard UTF-8)
  - **PDF** (via QuestPDF library)
- Exports preserve sorting and filtering context.

### UI Enhancements
- Clean, modern **Bootstrap 5** responsive layout.
- Visual feedback (alerts, success toasts, pagination controls).
- Role-aware navigation and user greetings.

---

## 👤 Identity & Role Management
### Authentication
- Built on **ASP.NET Core Identity** with user registration, login, and secure sessions.
- **Password policy:** minimum 8 characters, includes digits, optional uppercase/non-alphanumeric.
- **Lockout policy:** automatic lockout after 5 failed login attempts.

### User Profiles
- **Profile Page** where users can:
  - Update **Display Name** (used for navbar greetings).
  - Change password securely.
- Independent validation for each form (no cross-validation errors).

### Admin Management
- Admin-only **Manage Users** page allows:
  - Viewing all users with **Email**, **Display Name**, and **Admin role status**.
  - Adding or removing Admin privileges dynamically.
- Admin role created and assigned automatically on first run:
  - Email: `admin@demo.local`
  - Password: `Admin123!`
  - Roles: `Admin`, `Owner`

---

## 🔒 Security & API Protection
- **Global CSRF tokens** enforced on write operations (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE).
- **Rate limiting** for API writes (30 requests/minute window).
- **HSTS + HTTPS redirection** in production.
- **Role-based authorization** for admin-only pages.
- **Swagger** enabled only in Development for API testing.
- Built-in **antiforgery validation** using endpoint filters.

---

## ⚙️ DevOps & Testing
- CI pipeline (GitHub Actions) includes:
  - Build, Test, and CodeQL static analysis.
- Code-first EF migrations for schema control.
- InMemory provider available for test mode.
- `dotnet test` validates CRUD and alert logic.

---

## 🧠 Technology Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|--------|-------------|
| **Frontend** | Razor Pages, Bootstrap 5 |
| **Backend** | ASP.NET Core 8 |
| **ORM** | Entity Framework Core (Code First) |
| **Database** | SQL Server (LocalDB for dev) |
| **Export** | QuestPDF, CSV builder |
| **Authentication** | ASP.NET Core Identity |
| **CI/CD** | GitHub Actions + CodeQL |
| **Testing** | xUnit / MSTest / NUnit |

---

## 🧾 Database Design

### **Products**
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| Id | int | Primary Key |
| Name | nvarchar(200) | Required |
| Owner | nvarchar(100) | Required |
| Category | nvarchar(100) | Optional |
| Model | nvarchar(100) | Optional |
| Price | decimal(18,2) | Required |
| CreatedOn | datetime2 | Auto-set |

### **PriceHistories**
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| Id | int | PK |
| ProductId | int (FK) | Linked to Products |
| OldPrice | decimal(18,2) | Before change |
| NewPrice | decimal(18,2) | After change |
| ChangedOn | datetime2 | UTC timestamp |

### **Alerts**
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| Id | int | PK |
| ProductId | int (FK) | Linked to Products |
| OldPrice | decimal(18,2) | Previous price |
| NewPrice | decimal(18,2) | New price |
| DeltaPercent | decimal(5,2) | Percentage change |
| Message | nvarchar(max) | Alert message |
| CreatedAt | datetime2 | UTC |

---

## 🌐 API Endpoints Summary

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `/api/products` | GET | List all products |
| `/api/products/{id}` | GET | Get single product |
| `/api/products` | POST | Create new product |
| `/api/products/{id}` | PUT | Update existing product |
| `/api/products/{id}` | DELETE | Delete product |
| `/api/products/search` | GET | Filter by price/date range |
| `/api/products/export.csv` | GET | Export all products to CSV |
| `/api/products/export.pdf` | GET | Export all products to PDF |
| `/api/products/{id}/history/export.csv` | GET | Export price history to CSV |
| `/api/products/{id}/history/export.pdf` | GET | Export price history to PDF |
| `/api/alerts` | GET | View recent alerts |
| `/api/reports/summary` | GET | Summary dashboard (totals, alerts, top categories) |

---

## 🧭 Navigation Pages Overview

- **Index** – product list with search, filters, sorting, pagination.  
- **Create/Edit/Delete** – full CRUD with validation and alert triggers.  
- **Details/History** – individual product and its price changes.  
- **Dashboard** – total counts, total inventory value, top categories, alerts.  
- **Alerts** – shows all generated price alerts.  
- **Profile** – edit display name and change password.  
- **Admin → Users** – list all users and toggle Admin role.  
- **Swagger (dev only)** – API documentation and testing portal.

